{
  "stem": "20142.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We-- there were Jews in prison, and they were identified by a yellow triangle they were wearing on their chests.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they had to respond to the number.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I don't remember the number of my [? staying ?] at Pawiak, but I do remember that there were all kinds of people, and primarily people between the ages of 25 and 45, young Polish people.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And among them, there were some priests.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we knew that they were priests because they were allowed to conduct services on Sunday for the other prisoners.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were some Jewish prisoners.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[BACKROUND NOISE] And as I mentioned, it was easy to identify them because of the yellow triangle they were wearing on the left side of the chest.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was no such thing as celebration in anything, not even, not the only holiday.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But you were celebrating because you were getting up the next morning.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And coming back from my interrogation, Aleja Szucha from the gestapo headquarter.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One day, I was very, very fortunate that they just grabbed me out-- out of the cell.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I did not go for that day for interrogation.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there was a group of youngsters already working in outside, and they were shipping coal.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In other words, transporting coal from the-- from the railroad tracks to the gestapo headquarter.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was on a daily basis done constantly, without stop.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "This kind of work took part from 7 o'clock in the morning until 11 o'clock at night.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "From time to time, they were [? feeling ?] [? out ?] quite well, but nevertheless our backs were breaking on us, to the point that we couldn't just straighten out.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That's how I got out of Pawiak.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There was a miracle.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
